gomodel:SYNGO_4808  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: The N-terminal longin domain of C9orf72 interacts with the conserved C domain of synapsins.\n\nFigure 7: Loss of C9orf72 strongly reduced synaptic vesicle pools in the hippocampus in vivo, as shown by transmission electron micrographs of the CA3 region of the hippocampus from 12-week old C9orf72-WT or C9orf72-KO mice.. Experimental description: Figure 7: \"12-week old C9orf72-WT or C9orf72-KO mice\"\n\nknockout:\n\"C9orf72 KO mice were generated using the Cre-LoxP system. A foxed mouse line for the conditional deletion of C9orf72 exons 3-4, coding for the two C9orf72 ATG start codons, was generated in a mixed C57BL/6 and 129Sv strain (GenOway S.A., France)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
